'''''Jonathan''''' is a 1970 West German horror film directed by [[Hans W. Gei<U+00DF>end<U+00F6>rfer]]. The film stars J<U+00FC>rgen Jung, Hans-Dieter Jendreyko and Paul Albert Krumm. The film takes place in the 16th century where vampires who are immune to sunlight have taken over the world. Human rebels band together for a battle of life and the control of the civilization.<ref name="Browning" />


==Release==
''Jonathan'' was released in May 17, 1970 in West Germany.<ref name="filmportal.de">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmportal.de/en/movie/jonathan_ea43d4a6a2295006e03053d50b37753d|work=filmportal.de|title=Jonathan|accessdate=December 25, 2012}}</ref> Director Hans W. Gei<U+00DF>end<U+00F6>rfer won the Film Award in Gold at the [[Deutscher Filmpreis]] for Best New Direction for his work on ''Jonathan''.<ref name="filmportal.de" />


